<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Mirriana_00 on 06-03-2001 06:31 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">The best two ways you can think of to bully guilds into your alliance are both bannable.  I'd certainly think twice about joining with someone who told people to do those things.  That whole "He who fights monsters should be wary lest a monster he becomes" thing.

Uber guilds are largely independent, and don't need your rez, group, or ports.

Lets see:

1. Do your best to hinder them.  No grouping/rezing/porting/etc.
Drawback:  They do not need you for these.  Maybe it makes them go out of their way a little to get their own cleric there, but you likely would need these from them more than they need it from you.

2. Don't help them on their raids.
Drawback: They don't need your help.

3. FD training.
Drawback: You get banned.

4. Tell spamming.
Drawback: Everyone who does it gets banned.

5. KSing them whenever they plan a raid.
Drawback: You aren't uber and can't KS.  They laugh at you and let you help them kill the mob.  You then get banned for trying to KS.

6. PLoot their mobs.
Drawback: You get banned.

7. Call PNP on them.
Drawback: GMs will not back this on non-30 minute mobs.  Your guild can't kill the uber mob anyways.

8. Gather an equal force and petition to allow both sides to roll for the right to fight the mob.
Drawback: Your guild likely cannot kill a lot of mobs they fight, or have excessive downtime doing so.  At best you get half the kills and piss them off.

On a blue server there is basically nothing you can do to another person to stop what they are doing, besides things that will get you banned.  If you are so intelligent and creative, please list a way you can make a player do what you want without getting you banned.

"You think they aren't gonna listen when every other guild on the server is crawling down their necks and forcing them to go on the list???"

Crawling down their neck in this game is either stopped by a simple /ignore command or considered harrassment and bannable.  Forcing someone to do anything is therefor impossible.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
